  "biography_html": "<div class=\"research-section\">\n<p class=\"research-text\">Parmenon the Iambic Poet was a 4th-century BCE author. The 10th-century Byzantine encyclopedia, the Suda, identifies him as an iambic poet and grammarian from either Byzantium or Heraclea.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">The Suda records two lost works: a collection titled Iambs and a grammatical treatise, On the Ionic Dialect. Parmenon represents a later practitioner of the iambic tradition who also engaged in scholarly study of the Ionic dialect, the very medium of his poetry.</p>\n<p class=\"research-text\">His preserved entry in the Suda secures his place, however minor, in the history of Greek literature and Byzantine scholarship.</p>\n</div>",
